Gaupol 0.25.1
=============

 [X] Use Gtk.render_layout instead of deprecated Gtk.paint_layout to
     render line length margin in text views
 [X] Add GTK+ to list of dependencies in the README file (GTK+ has
     always been a dependency, its explicit mention was just forgotten
     when migrating from PyGTK to PyGObject)
 [X] Remove non-functional speech recognition menu item
     - https://www.mail-archive.com/gaupol-list@gna.org/msg00069.html

Gaupol 1.0
==========

 * Check AppData screenshots
   - http://blogs.gnome.org/hughsie/2013/10/08/how-to-take-169-screenshots/
 * Update wiki page to use new template
   - https://wiki.gnome.org/Apps/Template
 * Apply new GNOME goals?
   - https://wiki.gnome.org/Initiatives/GnomeGoals/PortToGtkApplication
   - https://wiki.gnome.org/Initiatives/GnomeGoals/PortToGMenu
   - https://wiki.gnome.org/Initiatives/GnomeGoals/HeaderBars
 * Migrate away from Gtk.Action, Gtk.UIManager, stock icons, etc.
   - https://mail.gnome.org/archives/gtk-devel-list/2013-July/msg00016.html
 * Allow using multiple dictionaries for spell-check
 * Add a GStreamer-based audio waveform display
